          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Australia-Nauru deal</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-10-2.jpg" alt="Australia-Nauru deal" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Australia and Nauru have <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/australia-nauru-ink-landmark-security-deal/a-70998063" target="_blank">signed</a> a landmark security treaty to counter China’s growing influence in the Pacific. The treaty requires Nauru to consult Australia before making agreements on security, defense, or critical infrastructure and grants Canberra oversight of Nauru’s ports, airfields, and banking sector. In exchange, Australia will provide nearly $64 million in financial aid over five years and ensure access to banking services for Nauru. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese emphasized the treaty’s importance for regional stability as China strengthens <a href="https://theconversation.com/chinas-increasing-political-influence-in-the-south-pacific-has-sparked-an-international-response-222105" target="_blank">ties</a> with Pacific nations, including the <a href="https://apnews.com/article/china-solomon-islands-us-taiwan-pacific-dc2e984ec5045060524c644ebf62b910" target="_blank">Solomon Islands</a> and <a href="https://english.www.gov.cn/statecouncil/leaders/202205/27/content_WS6290d195c6d02e533532b6c5.html" target="_blank">Kiribati</a>. For security and partly economic reasons, the South Pacific is an area of <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2022/06/06/asia/china-pacific-islands-wang-yi-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">competition</a> between China and the West, particularly Australia and the US.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
