          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇾🇪 Yemen:</strong>    
          Yemeni men are being <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/yemenis-forcefully-recruited-to-fight-for-russia-in-ukraine/a-70988973" target="_blank">lured</a> to Russia under false promises of lucrative jobs but are forced to fight in Ukraine, according to multiple witnesses and human rights organizations. Recruiters exploit the economic despair of Yemen and offer contracts written in unfamiliar languages and misleading terms. Upon arrival, the men face abusive conditions, lack of medical care, and danger on the battlefield. The <a href="https://samrl.org/home.php?l=e/10/A/c/1" target="_blank">Yemeni SAM Organization</a> reports recruitment is facilitated by intermediaries linked to the Houthi militia and Russian operatives.</p>
        </mj-text>
