          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇬🇭 Ghana:</strong>   
          Ghana’s Vice-President Mahamudu Bawumia <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cdx9nlyjke4o" target="_blank">conceded</a> defeat to the opposition leader and former President John Mahama in a tightly contested election, citing internal party tallies showing Mahama’s decisive win. The polls come during Ghana’s worst economic crisis in decades, with soaring inflation, unemployment, and debt struggles fueling calls for change. While the elections were largely peaceful, the election saw sporadic violence and delays in result announcements. Mahama will be sworn in on January 7, 2025.</p>
        </mj-text>
